## 1)  project:- Personal Voice Assistant :- Jarvis 

A Python-based personal voice assistant that can listen to voice commands and perform various tasks. 
The assistant uses speech recognition and text-to-speech to interact with the user in real time.

✨ Features
•Speech-to-text recognition
•Text-to-speech responses
•Executes common tasks (open apps, search online, tell time, etc.)
•User-friendly and customizable

🛠️ Tech Stack
•Language: Python
•Libraries: speech_recognition, pyttsx3, datetime, os, webbrowser (and more)

🚀 Future Improvements
•Add support for more advanced commands
•Integrate with APIs (weather, news, etc.)
•Build a GUI for better interaction


## 2) Project:- AI Based Auto Responder (WhatsApp Bot)

🔹 Overview
This project is an AI-powered auto responder for WhatsApp built using Python. 
It is designed to automatically reply to incoming WhatsApp messages in real time with intelligent and context-aware responses. 
The bot reduces manual effort by handling repetitive queries, improving response time, and ensuring seamless communication


🔹 Features
✅ Automated Replies – Responds instantly to incoming last messages.
✅ AI-Powered – Generates smart, human-like responses using chatgpt .
✅ Custom Rules – Allows predefined rules for specific keywords or phrases.
✅ Real-Time Interaction – Works seamlessly with WhatsApp Web.
✅ Scalable – Can be extended for business use (customer support, FAQs, etc.).

•Tech Stack
Programming Language: Python 🐍
Libraries/Frameworks:
Selenium (for WhatsApp Web automation)

🔹 Future Enhancements

•Integration with advanced AI models (e.g., GPT-based).
•Support for multimedia (images, voice notes).
•Dashboard for monitoring conversations.
•Multi-user support for businesses.


## 3) Project:- 
📊 Super Store Sales Dashboard – Key Insights

🔹 Project Description
This project is a Power BI Dashboard built for analyzing Super Store sales performance. 
The dashboard provides interactive insights into sales, profit, customer behavior, and product performance across multiple categories and regions.

🔹 Tools Used
Power BI – For building interactive visualizations
Excel/CSV Dataset – Data source for sales transactions

🔹 Key Features
• Overall KPIs – Total Sales, Profit, Revenue, Quantity Sold, and Customers
• Sales by Payment Mode – Distribution across Cards, Online, and COD
• Sales by Segment – Analysis for Consumer, Corporate, and Home Office segments
• Monthly Trends (YoY) – Comparison of Sales & Profit across 2019 and 2020
• Category & Sub-Category Insights – Top-performing product categories (Office Supplies, Technology, Furniture) and sub-categories (Phones, Chairs, Binders)
• Regional Analysis – Filter data by Central, East, South, and West regions

🔹 Business Insights
• COD accounts for the highest share of transactions.
• Consumer segment contributes nearly half of the total sales.
• Phones and Office Supplies are the top revenue generators.
• Sales and profits significantly increased in the last quarter of 2020 compared to 2019.

• Overall KPIs (Key Performance Indicators):
Total Sales: $1.57M
Total Profit: $175.26K
Quantity Sold: 22K units
Total Revenue: $7.18M
Total Customers: 5901

• Sales by Payment Mode:
Cards: 21.99%
Online: 35.38%
Cash on Delivery (COD): 42.62%

• Sales by Segment:
Home Office: 19%
Consumer: 48%
Corporate: 33%

• Monthly Sales by Year (YoY):
Trend comparison between 2019 & 2020.
Sales in 2020 show higher growth compared to 2019, especially in later months.

• Monthly Profit by Year (YoY):
Profits fluctuate across months.
Noticeable increase in profitability in the last quarter of 2020 compared to 2019.

• Sales by Category:
Office Supplies: $0.64M
Technology: $0.47M
Furniture: $0.45M

• Sales by Sub-Category:
Phones: $0.20M
Chairs: $0.18M
Binders: $0.17M

• Regional Filters Available:
Dashboard can be filtered by Central, East, South, and West regions.
